roblems.\n21. Variational inequalities and their application in optimal control problems.\n22. The principle of Pontryagin\'s maximum. Linear and nonlinear systems.\n23. Problems of root mean square estimation.\n24. Kalman-Bussey filter.\n25. Projection methods for solving operator equations.\n26. Iterative methods for solving operator equations.\n27. Integral transformations in mathematical modeling.\n28. Stochastic experiment. Algebras and sigma-algebras of random events. Axioms of probability theory.\n29. Random variables, their distributions and densities (examples). Key features 30. Selective method in statistics. Problems of parametric and nonparametric evaluation. Confidence intervals for parameters and random variables. Chebyshev and Gauss inequalities.\n31. The method of maximum probability.\n32. Methods of moments and least squares. Regression models 33. Methods of stochastic optimization.34. Partition theorems in problems of optimal control of stochastic systems.\n35. Differential games.\n36. Models and methods of queuing.\n37. Mathematical models of decision making in conditions of uncertainty.\n38. Interpolation and extrapolation of functions.\n39. Splines, cubic splines. Theorems on the best approximation.\n40. Models and methods of simulation. Event and processional approaches.\n41. Finite-difference methods for solving differential equations. Numerical stability of the difference solution scheme.\n42. Mathematical models of knowledge representation and manipulation in knowledge engineering.\n43. Principles of machine modeling and organization of calculations using a computer. Procedural languages ​​and directions of their development.\n44. Technology and programming techniques (based on FORTRAN, PASCAL, C or C ++). Data types. Operators. Functions and procedures. Memory classes. Input - output data. Data structures (lists, stacks and queues, arrays, sets, tables, trees, graphs). Search in linear lists. The task of choice. Binary search trees. Working with files (access, processing, sorting files). Programming tools. The concept of an integrated environment and its capabilities (for example, Borland Pascal or Borland C ++).\n45. Principles of object-oriented programming. Classes, objects, relations.\n46. ​​PC software. Operating systems (MS-DOS, WINDOWS-95, OS / 2 or UNIX). Text editors (Lexicon, Tex or Word). Graphic editors (PointBrush or CorelDraw). Database management systems (FoxBase, FoxPro or Paradox) 47. Integrated software (application packages, \"Mathematics\", MATCAD, etc., decision support systems, expert systems).\n\nBasic literature\n1. AD Myshkis, Elements of the Theory of Mathematical Models, Moscow; IF \"Physical and Mathematical Literature\", 1994. 192 pp.\n2. Kolmogorov AN, Fomin SV Elements of the theory of functions and functional analysis, 5th ed.— M .; Science, 1981. 420 pp.\n3. Lusternik LA, Sobolev VI Elements of functional analysis. - М .: Наука, 1982. 380 с 4. Kollatz L. Functional analysis and calculatorная математика— М .: Мир, 1969, 385 с 5. Marchuk GI Methods of computational mathematics. M .: Science. 1980, 420 pp.\n6. Beiko IV, Bublik BN, Zinko II. N. Methods and algorithms for solving optimization problems.— K .: Higher School, 1983, 512 pp.\n7. Tikhonov LP, Samara LL Equations of mathematical physics. —M: Nauka, 1977, 490 pp.\n8. Forsythe J. et al. Machine methods of mathematical calculations M. - Mir, 1980, 428 pp.\n9. Tyurin Yu. N., Makarov AA Data analysis on a computer - M .: Imfo-M \"Finance and Statistics\", 1995, 385 pp.\n10. Papadimitriou X., Staiglitz K. Combinatorial optimization. Algorithms and complexity.— M .: Mir. 1985, 524 pages 11. Shannon R. Simulation modeling of systems. - Art and science. - М .: Мир, 1978, 318 с 12. Ermoliev Yu. M., Lyashko II, Mikhalevich VS, Tyuntya VI Mathematical methods of operations research.— K .: Higher school, 1979, 281 pp.\n13. Ermoliev Yu. M. Methods of stochastic programming. M .: - Nauka, 1976, 312 pp.\n14. Vasiliev FP Methods for solving extreme problems - M .: Nauka, 1981, 298 pp.\n15. Pshenichny BN, Danilin Yu. M. Numerical methods in extremal problems. - М .: Наука, 1975, 340 с 16. Lyon J.-L. Optimal control of systems described by partial differential equations. M .: Mir, 1972, 315 pp.\n17. Bellman R., Dreyfus S. Applied problems of dynamic programming. - М .: Наука, 1987, 402 с 18. Pontryagin LS, Boltyansky VG, Gamkrelidze PV, Mishchenko EF Mathematical theory of optimal processes.— Moscow: Nauka, 1969. 490 pp.\n19. Shore N. 3. Methods for minimizing undifferentiable functions and their applications.— K .: Naukova Dumka, 1979, 315 pp.\n20. Sergienko IV Mathematical models and methods for solving problems of discrete optimization.— K .: Naukova Dumka, 1985, 318 pp.\n21. Krasovsky NN, Subbotin AI Positional differential games. - М .: Наука, 1974, 480 с 22. Samara AA, Gulin AV Numerical methods. - М .: Наука, 1989, 512 с 23. Zelkovets M., Shaw L., Gannon J. Principles of software development.— M .: Mir, 1982, 315 pp.\n24. Schleer S., Meller S. Object-oriented analysis. Modeling of the world in states, - K .: Dialektika, 1993, 240 pp.\n25. Martin J. Organization of databases in computer systems. - М .: Мир, 1978, 615 с 26. Representation and use of knowledge (X. Ueno, G. Koyama, etc.) lane. in Japanese. - M .: Mir. 1989, 312 pp.\n38. Encyclopedia of Cybernetics in 2 volumes - K .: Encyclopedia, 1974.\n39. Bublik BM, Kirichenko MF Fundamentals of control theory. - K. Higher school, 1975\n\nAdditional literature\n1. Kuzmichev DA, Radkevich IA, Smirnov AD Automation of experimental research: A textbook for universities - M .: Nauka, 1983, 302 pp.\n2. Riss F, Sekefalvi-Nagy B. Lectures on functional analysis. - M .: Mir. 1979, 360 pp.\n3. Vladimirov VS Equations of mathematical physics - M .: Nauka, 1988. 402 pp.\n4. Akhiezer NI, Glazman IM Theory of linear operators in Hilbert space.— Kharkiv: Higher school, 1977, 390 pp.\n5. Ermakov SI, Zhiglyavsky AA Mathematical theory of optimal experiment.— Moscow: Nauka, 1987, 398 pp.\n6. Gorsky VG, Adler Yu. P., Talalai AM Planning of industrial experiments (dynamics models) .— Moscow: Metallurgy, 1987, 112p.\n7. AD Tsvirkun et al. Simulation modeling in structure synthesis problems of complex systems: an optimization-simulation approach.— Moscow: Nauka, 1985, 174 pp.\n9. Tsikritzis D., Lokhovsky F. Data models, - M; Finance and Statistics, 1985. 344 pp.\n10. Date K. Introduction to database systems. - М .: Наука, 1980. 442с 11. Dovgal SN, Litvinov B. Yu., Sbitnev AI Personal computers: Turbo Pascal U.0.0. Object programming. Local area networks. Uch. allowance. - К .: Информсистема сервис, 1993, 430 с.\n\nThe program was developed by the author\'s team consisting of: Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences, Professor SI Lyashko, Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences, Professor OG Nakonechny (Taras Shevchenko Kyiv State University), Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences , Professor IB Sirodzha (Kharkiv Aviation Institute). The program is agreed with the scientific and methodical commission of the Ministry of Education of Ukraine. APPROVED by the Higher Attestation Commission of Ukraine and the Certification Board of the Ministry of Education of Ukraine on June 25, 1998 № 3 / 9—2 / 3.\n\n</div>', 'Typical program of the candidate exam MM and CM', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'typical-program-of-the-candidate-exam-mm-and-cm__trashed', '', '', '2021-06-04 21:48:41', '2021-06-04 21:48:41', '', 0, 'https://scs.wp.its-my.site/?page_id=183', 35, 'page', '', 0),
(184, 1, '2021-03-15 14:49:15', '2021-03-15 14:49:15', '<div class=\"field-item even\">\n<h3>Theoretical foundations</h3>\n1. Algebra of sets and relations. Algebraic systems, models, algebras. Generating sets: systems of generating and systems of defining relations. Congruences.\n\n2. Monobasic and polybasic universal algebras. Structures. Lattices. Boolean algebras. Categories. Topos.\n\n3. Formal languages ​​and theories. Numbering of statements. Executable and general formulas. Gödel\'s theorem on incompleteness.\n\n4. Counting predicates. Normal shape. Erbran\'s theorem. Resolution method. Lambda calculus. The concept of redex. Church-Rosser theorem.\n\n5. Basic computational operators. Primitive-recursive, general-recursive and partial-recursive functions. Thesis Church-Turing-Post-Wedge. The universal machine theorem and the s-m-n theorem. Wedge\'s fixed point theorem.\n\n6. Algorithmically unsolvable problems. Stop problem. Church\'s theorem on unsolvable derivation recognition problems in numerous first-order predicates. Rice\'s theorem on property recognition.\n\n7. The concept of a finite automaton. Homomorphism and isomorphism of automata. Minimization of machines. Finished automata and their connection with regular languages. Analysis and synthesis of finite automata. Discrete converters. Systems of algorithmic algebras VM Glushkova.\n\n8. Formal grammars. Classification of languages ​​according to Chomsky. Syntax and semantics of formal languages. Algorithms for determining the regularity of grammar. Context-free languages ​​and their connection with vending machines. Chomsky\'s normal form. Greybach\'s normal form. Context-free language as a solution of the equation. Analysis and synthesis of vending machines.\n\n9. Top-down parsing. LL (k) -grammar. Recursive descent. Bottom-up parsing. Grammar of precedence.\n\n10. Discrete systems and tasks of their implementation. Examples of discrete systems. Counts. Petri nets.\n\n11. The complexity of algorithms and calculations. NP-complex and NP-complete problems. Gradient methods, heuristic search, linear and dynamic programming, coloring the vertices of the graph, the problem of the salesman.\n<h3>Architecture of information processing systems.</h3>\n1. Logical design and principles of the computer: memory and its addressing; processor, command system and scheme of its operation; external devices and the concept of a common bus; interrupt.\n\n2. Control of external devices: keyboard (checking characters in the buffer, reprogramming individual keys); display (cursor control, display of characters on the screen, shift of the screen and page); disk drives (reading the table of file placement, working with files); printer (setting print specifications, linking data to the printer); input / output (serial port access, device driver creation).\n\n3. Methods of organization and classification of systems of parallel information processing: combination in time of different stages of different problems, simultaneous solution of different problems or parts of one problem; conveyor information processing; systems with a single stream of commands and multiple data streams; systems with multiple instruction flow and single data flow; systems with multiple command flow and multiple data flow.\n\n4. The concept of computing. Multi-machine complexes: weakly connected, directly connected, satellite. Multiprocessor complexes: with a common bus, with cross-switching, high-speed RAM. Features of the organization of computational processes in complexes. Comparison of multi-machine and multiprocessor complexes.\n\n5. The concept of computer system. Systems with conveyor information processing; matrix systems; associative systems and cells; functionally distributive systems; systems with a restructured structure. SIMD and MIMD architecture.\n\n6. The concept of computer network and its structure. Network characteristics: operational capabilities, message delivery time, performance and cost of data processing. Processes. Control levels. Interfaces. Message structure. Protocols. Methods and means of switching and data transmission. Addressing, packet routing and data flow management. Transport service. High-level protocols. Administrative management. Local area networks.\n<h3>Operating systems</h3>\n1. Operating systems (OS): purpose and basic concepts.\n\n2. File system; external device drivers; command language processor. Command files. System configuration.\n\n3. Structure and functions of MS-DOS: basic I / O system; the initial boot unit, the module of expansion of the basic system of input-output, the module of processing of interrupts, the command processor; MS-DOS utilities.\n\n4. Organization of program interaction through interrupts. Dynamic loading. Download and run software overlays. Resident programs.\n\n5. Hardware, logical and software interrupts. Writing your own break; addition to the existing oneabout interrupt.\n\n6. Organization of multiprogram processors. Formation of processes. Software for computers and multiprocessor systems.\n\n7. Structure and functions of UNIX OS.\n\n8. Windows environment. Basic classes of windows. Controls, buttons, input focus. Objects. Scripting.\n<h3>Programming languages ​​and systems</h3>\n1. Procedural and problem-oriented languages: features of the organization and directions of development. Basic concepts and possibilities of Fortran, Pascal, Module-2, C, C ++, Ada, Lisp, Prologue languages.\n\n2. Translators (assemblers and compilers) and interpreters. Stages of translation: lexical, syntactic, semantic analysis, optimization, object code generation, compilation.\n\n3. Memory management in the program created by the translator: static, automatic, basic and dynamic memory. Geshing methods.\n\n4. Organization of parameter transfer between software modules. Call by value, by name, by result. Problems of complexing multilingual modules.\n\n5. Languages ​​that focus on parallel and distributed processing. Features of implementation.\n\n6. Generators of programming systems. Macrogenerators and extensible programming systems, preprocessors.\n\n7. Programming metasystems: multilingual systems, parametric systems and metatranslators.\n\n8. Dialog programming systems: purpose and architecture. Forms of dialogue organization. Ways of language communication: video forms, menus, spreadsheets, use of function keys, etc .. Dialogue in natural language.\n<h3>Software programming and design technology</h3>\n1. The main stages and stages of program design and documentation. Terms of reference. Sketch, technical, working projects. Implementation and support. Software life cycle. Cascade and spiral models of the software life cycle.\n\n2. Program specification. Conceptual means of specification. Denotational, operational and axiomatic semantics. Classification of specification languages.\n\n3. Software quality. Methods of debugging and testing programs, program verification.\n\n4. Organization of work of teams of programmers. The team of the chief programmer. Software production planning. Designing serial and parallel programs.\n\n5. The concept of recursion. Recursive definitions and recursive programs. Properties of recursive algorithms. Functional and recursive data structures.\n\n6. Structural programming. Theorem on structuring programs. Multibasic algebras of data structures. Theoretical-multiple data structures.\n\n7. Schemes of programs over memory. Algebra of algorithms. Software reuse. Modifiability of algorithms and programs.\n\n8. Object-oriented programming. Languages: Smalltalk, C ++.\n\n9. Functional programming. Concepts and examples. Lisp language.\n\n10. Logic programming. Examples of programming systems \"by the rules\". Language Prologue.\n<h3>Database management systems</h3>\n1. General idea of ​​the database system: schemes and instances of data, physical database, data model, data scheme, subscheme. Designing a conceptual scheme. Data definition language. Database administrator. Data manipulation language. Data independence; data integrity and types of functional dependencies.\n\n2. Physical organization of data: model of organization of external memory, hashed and indexed files, B-trees, files with a dense index, files with records of variable length; partial matching search.\n\n3. Relational, network and hierarchical data model and their implementation; model comparison.\n\n4. Data manipulation languages ​​for the relational model: relational algebra and relational calculus; algebraic and calculus languages.\n\n5. Theory of relational database design: functional dependencies, decomposition of relationship schemes, normal forms of relationship schemes; multi-valued dependencies.\n\n6. Thesaurus in automated control systems and information processing.\n\n7. Data dictionary dictionaries: basic concepts, use, design issues, implementation strategies.\n\n8. Distributed databases: centralized and decentralized DBMS; database distribution problems; execution of requests; simultaneous processing and updating.\n\n9. Database machine as a hardware-programmable multiprocessor complex designed to perform database functions.\n<h3>Knowledge-based systems</h3>\n1. The concept of knowledge. The difference between the concepts of \"knowledge\" and \"data\". Knowledge base. Knowledge base programming systems.\n\n2. Models of knowledge representation: production, logical, network and frame.\n\n3. Methods of knowledge engineering: formalization of knowledge, replenishment of knowledge and exclusion of redundancy, generalization and classification, deductive inference; Bayesian theorem, inductive inference, processing of incomplete information, fuzzy inference. Problem solving planning, analogy and deduction.\n\n4. Languages ​​and knowledge representation systems: concepts and examples.\n\n5. The concept of expert system and its structure: database; knowledge base; solver (output machine); knowledge acquisition component; explanatory and dialogue component. Formalized and informal knowledge.\n\n6. Application packages (PPP): models, functions, mode of operation, architecture. System and functional filling of PPP and intermodule interface. Modular analysis of the subject area.\n\n7. Decision support systems and features of their implementation.\n\n8. Stages of development of knowledge-based systems: identification, conceptualization, formalization, implementation, testing, experimental operation, modification. Tools and methodology for developing knowledge-based systems, classification of tools.\n\n9. Principles of hardware development to support knowledge-based systems. Lisp processors and Prolog machines.\n<h3>Literature</h3>\n1. Agafonov VN Program specification: conceptual tools and their organization. - Novosibirsk: SSh izd-vo \"Nauka\", 1987. - 240 p.\n\n2. Architecture of multiprocessor computer systems / edited by Timokhin VI - L-d: LGU, 1961 - 104 p.\n\n3. Aho A., Ullman J. Theory of parsing, translation and compilation. T. 1, 2. - Mir, 1978. - 620 с.\n\n4. Bar R. The language of Hell in systems design. - М .: Мир, 1988. - 320 с.\n\n5. Borisov AN , Vivams EP , Sokur L.Ya. interactive decision-making systems based on mini-computers. - Riga: Zinatne, 1966.\n\n6. Bratko I. Programming in the language of the Prologue for artificial intelligence - M .: Mir, 1990. - 560 p.\n\n7. Brown P. Macroprocessors and software mobility. M.: Mir, 1977. - 254 s.\n\n8. Bryabrin VM Personal computer software. - М.: Наука, 1968. - 272 с.\n\n9. Vagin VN Deduction and generalization in decision making systems. - М.: Наука, 1968. - 384 с.\n\n10. Wagner P. Programming in the language of Hell. - М .: Мир, 1983.\n\n11. Velbitsky IV Programming technology. - Kiev: Technology,\n\n12. Wirth M. Programming in the language of Module-2. - М .: Мир, 1987.\n\n13. Gaek P., Gavranek T. Automatic formation of hypotheses. - М.: Наука, 1984. - 260с.\n\n14. Glushkov VM Fundamentals of paperless informatics - M .: Nauka, 1962. - 324 p.\n\n15. Glushkov VM , Zeitlin GE , Yushchenko EL Algebra. Languages. Programming. 3rd ed. Kiev: Science. Dumka, 1989.\n\n16. Gauthier R. UNIX Operating System Guide. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1965. - 232 с.\n\n17. Gris D. Designing compilers. - М .: Мир, 1976.\n\n18. Gris D. The science of programming. - М .: Мир, 1984.\n\n19. Davis W. Operating systems. - М .: Мир, 1960. - 346 с.\n\n20. Jehani N. Programming in C. - М .: Радио и связь, 1988\n\n21. Довгяло А.М. Dialogue between the user and the computer. Fundamentals of design and implementation. - Kiev: Science. thought, 1976. - 232 p.\n\n22. Zamorin AP etc. Computers, systems, complexes. - М.: Наука, 1985.\n\n23. Zamulin AV Database and knowledge programming systems. - М .: Наука, 1990.\n\n24. Zelkovets M., Shaw A., Gannon J. Principles of software development. - М .: Мир, 1982. - 368 с.\n\n25. Artificial intelligence. Handbook in 3 books. - М .: Радио и связь, 1990.\n\n26. Jensen K., Wirth N. Pascal. User guide and language description. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1982.\n\n27. Kapitonova Yu.V. , Letichevsky AA Mathematical theory of computer systems design. M.: Nauka, 1988. - 295 s.\n\n28. Kalinichenko LA , Ryvkin VM Database and knowledge machines. - М.: Наука, 1990 - 296 с.\n\n29. Kalinichenko LA Methods and means of integration of inhomogeneous databases. - М .: Наука, 1983.\n\n30. Kasyanov VN Optimizing program transformations. - М.: Наука, 1988. - 335 с.\n\n31. Klini SK Mathematical logic. - М .: Мир, 1973.\n\n32. Kozhevnikova GP Data structures and the design of an efficient computing environment. - Lviv: LSU Publishing House, 1986.\n\n33. L.V. Кокорева, О.Л. Перевозчикова, Е.Л. Yushchenko. Dialogue systems and knowledge representation. - Kiev: Scientific opinion. 1993 - 448 p.\n\n34. Королев Л.Н. The structure of computers and their mathematical support. - М.: Наука, 1978. - 352 с.\n\n35. Kotov VE Introduction to the theory of program schemes. Novosibirsk: Nauka, 1978. - 257 p.\n\n36. Kotov VE Remember Petri. - М.: Наука, 1984. - 160 с.\n\n37. Coates R., Vleimik I. Human-Computer Interface.\n\n38. Larionov AM , Mayorov SA , Novikov GI Computing systems, systems and networks. - LD: Energoatom ed. , 1967. - 288 p.\n\n39. Larichev OI , Mechitov AI , Moshkovich EM, Furems EM Identification of expert knowledge. - М .: Наука, 1989.\n\n40. Leong-Hong B. Dictionary systems - a reference book. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1986. - 311 с.\n\n41. Logical approach to artificial intelligence: from classical logic to logical programming / Tei A., Gribomon P., Louis J. et al. - M .:, 1990. - 632 p.\n\n42. Lorier J. - L. Artificial intelligence systems. - М .: Мир, 1990. - 568 с.\n\n43. Maltsev AI Algebraic systems. - М.: Наука, 1970. - 393 с.\n\n44. Maltsev AI Algorithms and recursive functions. M.: Nauka, 1966. - 368 s.\n\n45. Mednik S., Donovan J. Operating systems. M.: Mir 1979.\n\n46. ​​Melikhov AN , Bernstein LS , Korovin SY Situational advisory systems with odd logic. - М.: Наука, 1990. - 272 с.\n\n47. Object-oriented programming. Thematic issue. - Programming, 1992. - N2.\n\n48. Organization of expert systems / M. Stefik, J. Aikins, R. Balzer, J. Benoit, etc. // Cybernetic collection. - M .: Mir, 1985, issue. 22. - 170-2207\n\n49. Ore O. Graph theory. - М.: Наука, 1960. - 336 с.\n\n50. Osuga S. - Processing of knowledge. - Mir, 1969. - 293 p.\n\n51. Parasyuk IN , Sergienko IV Data analysis software packages: development technology. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1988. - 159 с.\n\n52. Representation and use of knowledge / X. Ueno, T. Koyama, T. Okamoto et al. - M .: Mir, 1989. - 220 p.\n\n53. Acquisition of knowledge / Ed. S. Osugi, Y. Saeki. - М: Мир, 1990. - 304 с.\n\n54. Personal computer software. / Stogniy AA, Ananyevsky SA, Barsuk Ya. I., etc. - Kiev: Naukova dumka, 1969. - 386 p.\n\n55. Sekarahan E. Database machines and database management. - М .: Мир, 1989. - 695 с.\n\n56. Parallel processing systems / Ed. D. Ivex. - М .: Мир, 1985.\n\n57. Database and knowledge management systems / Naumov AN, Vandrov AM , Ivanov VK and others / M. : изд. Finance and Statistics, 1991. - 352 p.\n\n58. Tyugu E.H. Conceptual programming. - М.: Наука, 1984. - 256 с.\n\n59. Uspensky VA , Semenov AL Theory of algorithms: basic discoveries and applications. - М.: Наука, 1987. - 288 с.\n\n60. Hunter P. Design and construction of compilers. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1984 - 232 с.\n\n61. Hoare C. Interacting successive processes. - М .: Мир, 1969. - 264 с.\n\n62. Hogger K. Introduction to logical programming. - М .: Мир, 1988. - 384 с.\n\n63. Hüvenen E. , Seppenek J. Mir Lispa: v 2 t. - M .: Mir, 1990. - T.1 - 447 s .; Т.2 - 319 с.\n\n64. Tsikritzis D., Lechowski F. Data models. - М.: Финансы и статистика, 1985. - 344 с.\n\n65. Chen Ch., Li R. Mathematical logic and automatic proof of theorems. - М.: Наука, 1983. - 358 с.\n\n66. Shemakin YI Thesaurus in automated control and information processing systems. - М .: Воензидат, 1974. - 188 с.\n\n67. Expert systems: principles of work and examples / Edited by R. Forsythe. - М .: Радио и связь, 1987. - 223 с.\n\n68. Elti J., Kumbe M. Expert systems: concepts and examples. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1987. - 191 с.\n\n69. Jakubaitis EA Information and computer networks. - М .: Финансы и статистика, 1964.\n\nThe program was developed by the author\'s team consisting of: Yushchenko KL - Corresponding Member of the NAS of Ukraine (Glushkov Institute of Cybernetics of the NAS of Ukraine), Perevozchikova OL - Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences (Glushkov Institute of Cybernetics of the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine), Parasyuk IM - Doctor of Technical Sciences (Glushkov Institute of Cybernetics of the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine).\n\nThe program is agreed with the scientific-methodical commission of the Ministry of Education of Ukraine.\n\nApproved by the Higher Attestation Commission of Ukraine \"May 16, 1995\" and the Attestation Board of the Ministry of Education of Ukraine \"