a href=\"https://scs.wp.its-my.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/images_ZahystDocs_Tabl_Bakalavr_2020.docx\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Шаблон таблиці з балами від керівника для бакалавра</span></a></strong>\n\n<a href=\"https://scs.wp.its-my.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/images_ZahystDocs_Vidguk_Keriv_Bakalavr-2020.docx\"><strong>Відгук керівника ДП</strong></a>\n\n<a href=\"https://scs.wp.its-my.site/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/images_ZahystDocs_Recensiya_DP_Bakalavr-2020.doc\"><strong>Рецензія на ДП</strong></a>\n<p align=\"center\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"color: #b22222;\"><strong>Не пізніше, ніж за 5 днів до захисту</strong></span></span></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>необхідно здати документи секретарю ЕК</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Кучмій Оксані Олександрівні (104/2-15к):</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n 	<li>Зброшурований та підписаний дипломний проєкт (роботу).</li>\n</ol>\n<ul class=\"rteindent1\">\n 	<li><strong><u>Титульний аркуш</u></strong> із зазначенням освітньо-професійної програми (відповідно до наказу на зарахування, див. вище) та спеціальності (<span style=\"color: #800080;\"><strong><u>123 «Комп\'ютерна інженерія»</u></strong></span>), теми, ПІБ студента, керівника, консультантів, рецензента і т.д., де <strong>мають бути всі підписи</strong>;</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ЗАВДАННЯ на ДП</u></strong> із обов’язковим зазначенням номеру та дати наказу(<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"\">N<u>1181-С</u></span></span>  від    <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"\"><u>25.05.2020</u></span></span>  р.) та календарним планом;</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>Анотації</u></strong> (українською та англійською  мовами на окремих аркушах)</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ОПИС АЛЬБОМУ</u></strong> (перший аркуш – з  великим кутовим штампом, де <strong>мають бути всі підписи</strong>);</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ТЕХНІЧНЕ ЗАВДАННЯ</u></strong> (перший аркуш – з великим кутовим штампом, де <strong>мають бути всі підписи</strong>);</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ВІДОМІСТЬ ТЕХНІЧНОГО ПРОЄКТУ</u></strong> (перший аркуш – з великим кутовим штампом, де <strong>мають бути всі підписи</strong>);</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ПОЯСНЮВАЛЬНА ЗАПИСКА</u></strong> (перший аркуш – з великим кутовим штампом, де мають бути всі підписи - ЗМІСТ), яка завершується СПИСКОМ ВИКОРИСТАНОЇ ЛІТЕРАТУРИ (відповідно до ДСТУ ГОСТ 7.1:2006) - НЕ МЕНШЕ 50 АРКУШІВ;</li>\n 	<li><strong><u>ДОДАТКИ</u></strong>:</li>\n</ul>\nграфічні матеріали – з великим кутовим штампом, де <strong>мають бути всі підписи</strong>,\n\nлістинг програм(-и));\n\n<strong>презентація</strong>.\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li>Компакт-диск з матеріалами дипломного проєкту (роботи).</li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 35.45pt;\">Інформація, записана на диск,  повинна бути структурована наступним чином:</p>\n\n<ul class=\"rteindent1\">\n 	<li>папка TEXT;</li>\n 	<li>папка GRAPH;</li>\n 	<li>папка PROGRAM;</li>\n 	<li>папка PREZENTATION</li>\n 	<li>папка WEBSITE (містить файл з анотаціями українською та англійською мовами, що розміщуватиметься на сайті кафедри).</li>\n</ul>\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>                           Назва кожного файлу повинна починатися з прізвища автора проєкту українською мовою!!!</strong></span>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 35.45pt;\">На диску повинен бути <strong>підпис керівника</strong>. Цей диск необхідно вкласти в конверт, що приклеюється до внутрішньої сторони обкладинки в кінці зброшурованого дипломного проекту.</p>\n\n<ol>\n 	<li value=\"4\">Зброшуровані копії слайдів презентації (4 примірники) - Не ПОТРІБНО в 2020 р.</li>\n 	<li value=\"5\">Рецензія обов\'язково з ПЕЧАТКОЮ.</li>\n 	<li value=\"6\">Відгук керівника (+таблиця з балами на окремому аркуші).</li>\n 	<li>Перша сторінка перевірки на плагіат в системі UNICHECK.</li>\n 	<li>Копії опублікованих статей, тез доповідей, актів (довідок) про впровадження (якщо такі є).</li>\n</ol>\nДетальнішу інформацію можна прочитати тут: <a href=\"http://www.fpm.kpi.ua/faculty/diploma.do\">http://www.fpm.kpi.ua/faculty/diploma.do</a>\n\n<strong>Після проходження нормоконтолю дипломний проєкт підписується завідувачем кафедри СПіСКС Романкевичем В.О.</strong> <strong>не пізніше, ніж за три дні до захисту</strong><strong> в 102-15 к.</strong>\n\n<strong>Особи, дипломний проєкт яких не підписаний завідувачем кафедри, до захисту НЕ ДОПУСКАЮТЬСЯ!</strong>\n\n<strong>За несвоєчасне подання вище зазначених документів, а також за оформлення їх в неналежному вигляді накладатимуться штрафні бали (див. табличку)</strong>\n\n<strong><u>Порядок підготовки дипломного проекту до захисту</u></strong>\n<ol>\n 	<li>Підшитий ДП і графічний матеріал підписується автором, керівником, рецензентом, відповідальним за нормоконтроль.</li>\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Диск з матеріалами ДП підписується керівником та приклеюється в конверті на обложці ДП. На адресу <a href=\"mailto:ok_kuch@i.ua\">ok_kuch@i.ua</a>  надсилається вміст теки WEBSITE. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Назва кожного файлу повинна починатися з прізвища автора проєкту українською мовою!!!</strong></span></span></li>\n 	<li>ДП разом з рецензією, відгуком та табличкою результатів оцінювання від керівника (посилання на зразок в електронному вигляді дивись вище) та графічними матеріалами надається секретарю екзаменаційної комісії (при умові надходження файлів по електронній пошті для розміщення матеріалів ДП на сайті кафедри).</li>\n 	<li>Затверджений завідувачем кафедри ДП разом з усією необхідною документацією остаточно здається секретарю екзаменаційної комісії.</li>\n 	<li>Матеріали ДП будуть розміщені на сайті кафедри.</li>\n 	<li>Захист ДП відбувається відповідно до графіку.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>', 'Документація до захисту - Бакалаври', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '194-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-06-04 21:47:25', '2021-06-04 21:47:25', '', 194, 'https://wp.scs.its-my.site/?p=980', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(981, 1, '2021-06-04 21:47:26', '2021-06-04 21:47:26', '<div class=\"field-item even\">\n<h3>Preface</h3>\nThe program of the candidate examination in the specialty \"Computer Systems and Components\" reflects the current state of this field and includes its most important sections, the knowledge of which is necessary for a highly qualified specialist.\n\nThe examinee must show a high level of theoretical and professional training, knowledge of general concepts and history of development, deep understanding of the main sections, as well as the ability to use their knowledge to solve research and applied problems in computer systems and components.\n\nThe program is based on the programs of the following disciplines studied at the Higher Technical School of Ukraine: \"Applied Theory of Digital Automata\", \"Programming\", \"System Programming\", \"Computer Electronics\", \"Computer Circuitry\", \"Computer Architecture\" \"Computer Systems\", \"System Software\", \"Peripherals\", \"Computer Networks\", \"Fundamentals of Automated Design of OT\", \"Fundamentals of Artificial Intelligence Systems Theory\", \"Parallel and Distributed Computing\" \",\" Operating systems \",\" Theoretical foundations of information and measurement technology \",\" Methods of measuring physical quantities \",\" Measuring transducers \",\" Analog measuring instruments \",\" Digital measuring instruments \",\" Fundamentals of metrology \",\" Electronics and chip technology \",\" Elements and devices of automation \",\" Theory of automatic control \",\" Computers and systems \", Metrology and measurement\", \"Microprocessor devices of automation\".\n<h4>The program includes the following sections:</h4>\n1. History of computers, systems, networks, and their components.\n\n2. Mathematical, arithmetic and logical foundations of computer technology.\n\n3. Computer architecture and principles of information processing.\n\n4. Computer systems.\n\n5. Computer networks.\n\n6. Theoretical foundations of component construction.\n\n7. Components of computers, systems and networks\n\n8. Computer and network software.\n\n9. Design of computers, systems and networks.\n\n10. Reliability of computers, systems and networks.\n\n11. Protection of information in systems and networks.\n\n12. Information and measuring systems and their components.\n<h3>1. History of computers, network systems and their components</h3>\n1.1. Stages of development of computer, control and measuring equipment and their components. Flynn\'s classification.\n\n1.2. Digital and analog computers: basic principles of construction and organization of the computing process.\n\n1.3. Classification of computers on various grounds. Table of parameters of TOP-500 computer systems.\n\n1.4. Development of integrated technologies, Moore\'s law and physical limitations of development of silicon technologies.\n\n1.5. New technologies for creating components and structures of computers (optical, cryoelectronic, biotechnology, etc.). Laws of Money, Amdal, etc.\n<h3>2. Mathematical, Arithmetic and Logic Fundamentals of Computer Engineering</h3>\n2.1 Algorithmic versatility of computers. Turing machine. Fundamentals of logic algebra. Methods of representation of systems of logical functions, methods of their minimization. Functional completeness of systems of logical functions. Analysis and synthesis of combinational schemes.\n\n2.2 Abstract automaton. Analysis and synthesis of finite automata. Minimize abstract automata.\n\n2.3 Presentation of information in computers. Number systems. Ways of presenting data. Representation of decimal numbers and letter information.\n\n2.4 Organization of arithmetic and logical operations and ways to accelerate them.\n<h3>3. Computer architecture and principles of information processing</h3>\n3.1 Architecture and structures of computers, and variants of their architectural - structural organization. Computer hardware and software platforms, their examples.\n\n3.2 Characteristics of computers (performance, reliability, reliability of information processing, ways of presenting information, capacity of random access memory and permanent storage device, etc.).\n\n3.4 Intensive and extensive computer structures (von Neumann-Lebedev model, computers with concentrated and dispersed hardware, computers with a programmable structure, architecture \"processor in memory\", etc.).\n\n3.5 Formation, extraction, presentation and processing of knowledge in computer systems. Basic definitions of knowledge management methods. Computers for working with algebra of complex data structures, lexicographic systems, text processing.\n\n3.6 Neural networks. Architectural features and functionality.\n<h3>4. Computer systems</h3>\n4.1 Varieties of computer systems and complexes. Classifications of Flynn, Erlanger, Shore, etc.\n\n4.2 Multi-machine and multiprocessor systems. Features of construction and use.\n\n4.3 Problem-oriented systems: knowledge-oriented, matrix, associative and other systems.\n\n4.4 Geographically distributed systems: purpose and principles of organization. Metacomputers and GRID-systems, architectural and structural organization and application features.\n\n4.5 Systems with reconfigured structure. Principles of organization, features of design and application.\n<h3>5. Computer Networks</h3>\n5.1 Reference model of open systems interaction (EMBBC). Seven-level architecture. Functions of levels and their interaction. Services, protocols, interfaces\n\n5.2 Physical data transmission media and their comparative characteristics. Shannon\'s theorem on the relationship between bandwidth and channel bandwidth.\n\n5.3 Technologies for switching channels, messages and packets. Logical and physical structure of networks.\n\n5.4 Transmitted data networks (MTDs). MTD architecture of types X.25, ISDN, Frame Relay, ATM, etc. International MTD standards.\n\n5.5 Local area networks: topology, architecture and structural organization. Access methods in networks such as Ethernet, Token Ring, FDDI, ATM. Package formats. Comparison of LAN characteristics.\n\n5.6 Corporate networks. Functions, algorithms and features of hubs, bridges, switches and routers. Router types and routing protocols. Network perimeter security.\n\n5.7 Internet: architecture and structural organization. TCP / IP protocol stack. Packet formats, addressing and routing in IP networks. Technology of WWW, Web-servers. Web pages, hypertext languages ​​such as HTML, XML, SGML, etc.\n<h3>6. Theoretical foundations of component construction</h3>\n6.1 Fundamentals of modeling theory. The concept of model, basic properties of models, classification of models. Modeling languages. Methods of processing simulation results.\n\n6.2 Elements of the theory of linear electric circuits: circuit currents, nodal potentials, matrix analysis. Analysis of nonlinear electric circuits.\n\n6.3 Transmitting, transient and amplitude-frequency characteristics. Analysis of component performance in time and frequency domains. Methods of stability analysis.\n\n6.4 Basic concepts of experimental research, observation, calculation, measurement, control, diagnosis.\n\n6.5 Physical quantities and signals, their mathematical description. Systematization of physical quantities. Classification of measurements: direct, indirect, indirect, cumulative and compatible.\n<h3>7. Components of computers, systems and networks</h3>\n7.1 Digital Components.\n\n7.1.1 Types of units and blocks of modern computers, their characteristics. Processors, memory and computational process control, I / O devices.\n\n7.1.2 Large integrated circuits (VIMS). Types and sets of VIMS. Their characteristics and manufacturing technologies.\n\n7.1.3 Programmable logic integrated circuits, features of their organization and use.\n\n7.1.4 Microprocessors: structure, internal languages, typical operations and procedures. Examples and characteristics of modern GP.\n\n7.1.5 Digital signal processors. Types and characteristics.\n\n7.1.6 Memory integrated circuits. Types of integrated storage devices (SD). ICs with random and sequential sampling on bipolar TIR transistors. Programmable and reprogrammed permanent FE. Comparative evaluation of modern static and dynamic RUs. ZP on devices with charge communication, on cylindrical domains, holographic, cryoelectronic ZP.\n\n7.2 Analog and analog-digital, digital-analog components.\n\n7.2.1 Operational amplifiers (OP). Analysis of OP schemes, their main parameters and characteristics. Temperature and time drifts. Drift compensation methods. Stability of OP schemes, their correction.\n\n7.2.2 Means of measuring equipment: measure, measuring transducer, scale transducer, comparator. Basic parameters and characteristics.\n\n7.2.3 Instrumental amplifiers, active filters, multipliers and modulators. Analog switches and memory circuits. Analog signal synthesizers.\n\n7.2.4 Sensors and transducers. Strain-sensitive elements, thermoelectric converters, thermocouples. Optoelectronic converters. Hall sensors, magnetoresistors, semiconductor quantum interferometers (SQUID).\n\n7.2.5 Digital-to-analog converters (ADC). Main components, characteristics and parameters. Analog-to-digital converters (ADC). ADC direct and compensatory transformations. Sigma-delta ADC. Basic parameters and characteristics.\n\n7.2.6 Converter errors. The reasons for their occurrence and their evaluation. Methods of mathematical description of sensitivity and accuracy of means of transformation. Deterministic and probabilistic methods of error estimation. Static and dynamic converter errors.\n<h3>8. Computer and network software</h3>\n8.1 Assemblers and their types. Machine-dependent and independent characteristics of assemblers. Assembler translators.\n\n8.2 Operating systems (OS). The main components and general characteristics of operating systems and their interfaces.\n\n8.3 Mecutting OS: architecture and functional features, administration. Information resource security. Archival backup technology. Spaces of development of distributed applications Delphi, Informix, Oracle, Power Builder, etc.\n\n8.4 Systems and programming languages. Machine-oriented, problem-oriented and universal programming languages. Alphabet, syntax and semantics. Ways to describe programming languages.\n\n8.5 Compilation and its phases. Compilers with optimization.\n<h3>9. Design of computer systems and networks</h3>\n9.1 System approach to computer design. Levels and stages of design.\n\n9.2 Tasks and methods of design. System, functional, logical, technical and technological design. The main tasks of equipment design on ultra-large integrated circuits.\n\n9.3 System of integration of computer tools as a development of a systems approach to design. General concept and definition.\n\n9.4 Basic design technologies: multi-agent technology. Web - technology, etc. Strategy for choosing compatible hardware and software. Integration of various hardware and software platforms for building computer systems.\n\n9.5 Modeling to substantiate the proposed technical solutions. Hardware description languages ​​(VHDL, Verilog, etc.).\n\n9.6 Ontology as a tool for designing computer systems.\n\n9.7 Design of functional blocks and elementary base of computers with the help of CAD. Basic CAD software packages (Design Lab, OrCad, PSpice, etc.)\n\n9.8 Features of designing reconfigured computer systems using FPGA.\n<h3>10. Reliability of computers, systems and networks</h3>\n10.1 Reliability indicators of computers, systems and networks. Influence of element base parameters on reliability indicators.\n\n10.2 Methods and ways to ensure high reliability of information processing.\n\n10.3 Reliability of information processing results in computers and networks, depending on failures and equipment failures.\n\n10.4 Hardware automatic control of computers and networks to ensure the accuracy of information processing.\n\n10.5 Methods of coding information and their application to increase the reliability of information processing.\n<h3>11. Information security in systems and networks</h3>\n11.1 Information security of computer processing and data storage. The main tasks of information security in computer systems and networks.\n\n11.2 Organizational, software and hardware means of information protection. Means of restricting access to information to protect computer systems and networks from unauthorized access attempts.\n\n11.3 Algorithms and programs for cryptographic data encryption. Special processors for cryptography. User ID.\n\n11.4 Computer viruses, their classification and distribution, methods of virus detection and means of protection against them. The most common virus protection packages.\n\n11.5 Copyright (including software) and means of protection.\n<h3>12. Information-measuring systems and their components</h3>\n12.1 Basic definitions of measuring equipment: measurement, physical quantity, measurement result, measurement error and its components, classification of measurement methods.\n\n12.2 Measuring instruments and their characteristics. Primary measuring transducers (PVD) and secondary measuring transducers (GDP). Their mistakes. VP bridge diagrams.\n\n12.3 Digital measuring devices (DSP). Frequency meters. Integrating CVP. CVP deploy transformations and follow-up CVPs.\n\n12.4 Microprocessor means and systems of automatic measurements.\n\n12.5 Basic metrological characteristics of CVP.\n<h3>References</h3>\n1. Azarov OD Fundamentals of the theory of analog-to-digital conversion based on redundant positional number systems. Vinnytsia: UNIVERSE. 2004-260 p.\n\n2. Ificher Emmanuel S., Jervis Barry W. Digital signal processing: a practical approach 2nd edition .: Per. with English - M .: Williams Publishing House, 2004 - 992 p.\n\n3. Alfeev VN, Bakhtin PY, Vasenkov AA, Voitovich ID, etc .. Integrated circuits and microelectronic devices on superconductors. M .: Radio i svyaz, 1985. - 232 p.\n\n4. Alnah IN Modeling of computer systems. 