(984, 1, '2021-06-04 21:48:41', '2021-06-04 21:48:41', '<div class=\"field-item even\">\n\n1. The concept of mathematical model and basic requirements. Areas and features of application of mathematical, machine and field modeling.\n2. Classification of mathematical models and methods of their construction.\n3. Scientific, engineering and industrial experiment as a means of constructing or refining a mathematical model of the object under study. Correctness and adequacy of the model.\n4. General scheme and basic methods of analysis, data structuring and experiment planning.\n5. Computational complexity of problems and algorithms. Classes of problems of polynomial and exponential complexity.\n6. Sets and operations on them. Display. Classes of sets. Ordered sets. Set systems\n\n7. Convex sets, operations on them and their properties. Separation theorems.\n8. Convex functions and their properties.\n9. Metric and topological spaces. Convergence. Completeness of metric spaces. The principle of compressive mappings. Compactness\n\n10. Ordinary differential equations and systems. Cauchy problem and boundary value problem, existence and unity of solution.\nBasic equations of mathematical physics. Classification of quasilinear differential equations. Statement of basic boundary value problems for second-order linear differential equations.\n12. Necessary conditions of extremum. Lagrange multiplier rule.\n13. Methods of unconditional optimization of differential functions in finite-dimensional spaces.\n14. Methods of conditional optimization of differentiation functions in finite-dimensional spaces.\n15. Methods of non-differential optimization.\n16. Methods of discrete and combinatorial optimization.\n17. Necessary conditions of extremum in problems of mathematical programming. Kuhn-Tucker theorem.\n18. Problems and methods of linear programming.\n19. Problems and methods of dynamic programming.\n20. The problem of optimal control. The problem of moments in optimal control problems.\n21. Variational inequalities and their application in optimal control problems.\n22. The principle of Pontryagin\'s maximum. Linear and nonlinear systems.\n23. Problems of root mean square estimation.\n24. Kalman-Bussey filter.\n25. Projection methods for solving operator equations.\n26. Iterative methods for solving operator equations.\n27. Integral transformations in mathematical modeling.\n28. Stochastic experiment. Algebras and sigma-algebras of random events. Axioms of probability theory.\n29. Random variables, their distributions and densities (examples). Key features 30. Selective method in statistics. Problems of parametric and nonparametric evaluation. Confidence intervals for parameters and random variables. Chebyshev and Gauss inequalities.\n31. The method of maximum probability.\n32. Methods of moments and least squares. Regression models 33. Methods of stochastic optimization.34. Partition theorems in problems of optimal control of stochastic systems.\n35. Differential games.\n36. Models and methods of queuing.\n37. Mathematical models of decision making in conditions of uncertainty.\n38. Interpolation and extrapolation of functions.\n39. Splines, cubic splines. Theorems on the best approximation.\n40. Models and methods of simulation. Event and processional approaches.\n41. Finite-difference methods for solving differential equations. Numerical stability of the difference solution scheme.\n42. Mathematical models of knowledge representation and manipulation in knowledge engineering.\n43. Principles of machine modeling and organization of calculations using a computer. Procedural languages ​​and directions of their development.\n44. Technology and programming techniques (based on FORTRAN, PASCAL, C or C ++). Data types. Operators. Functions and procedures. Memory classes. Input - output data. Data structures (lists, stacks and queues, arrays, sets, tables, trees, graphs). Search in linear lists. The task of choice. Binary search trees. Working with files (access, processing, sorting files). Programming tools. The concept of an integrated environment and its capabilities (for example, Borland Pascal or Borland C ++).\n45. Principles of object-oriented programming. Classes, objects, relations.\n46. ​​PC software. Operating systems (MS-DOS, WINDOWS-95, OS / 2 or UNIX). Text editors (Lexicon, Tex or Word). Graphic editors (PointBrush or CorelDraw). Database management systems (FoxBase, FoxPro or Paradox) 47. Integrated software (application packages, \"Mathematics\", MATCAD, etc., decision support systems, expert systems).\n\nBasic literature\n1. AD Myshkis, Elements of the Theory of Mathematical Models, Moscow; IF \"Physical and Mathematical Literature\", 1994. 192 pp.\n2. Kolmogorov AN, Fomin SV Elements of the theory of functions and functional analysis, 5th ed.— M .; Science, 1981. 420 pp.\n3. Lusternik LA, Sobolev VI Elements of functional analysis. - М .: Наука, 1982. 380 с 4. Kollatz L. Functional analysis and calculatorная математика— М .: Мир, 1969, 385 с 5. Marchuk GI Methods of computational mathematics. M .: Science. 1980, 420 pp.\n6. Beiko IV, Bublik BN, Zinko II. N. Methods and algorithms for solving optimization problems.— K .: Higher School, 1983, 512 pp.\n7. Tikhonov LP, Samara LL Equations of mathematical physics. —M: Nauka, 1977, 490 pp.\n8. Forsythe J. et al. Machine methods of mathematical calculations M. - Mir, 1980, 428 pp.\n9. Tyurin Yu. N., Makarov AA Data analysis on a computer - M .: Imfo-M \"Finance and Statistics\", 1995, 385 pp.\n10. Papadimitriou X., Staiglitz K. Combinatorial optimization. Algorithms and complexity.— M .: Mir. 1985, 524 pages 11. Shannon R. Simulation modeling of systems. - Art and science. - М .: Мир, 1978, 318 с 12. Ermoliev Yu. M., Lyashko II, Mikhalevich VS, Tyuntya VI Mathematical methods of operations research.— K .: Higher school, 1979, 281 pp.\n13. Ermoliev Yu. M. Methods of stochastic programming. M .: - Nauka, 1976, 312 pp.\n14. Vasiliev FP Methods f